ce:section.ce:para:
The mechanism of post-epoxidation treatment was based on the mature epoxidation method of olefin. As the π-electrons in the CC are more weakly influenced by nucleic attraction, olefin will readily provides its electrons and be oxidized. The CC bonds in GQDs were similar to those of olefin. Hence, within the BF4 ionic solution and under the catalysis of aqueous NaOH, 30% H2O2 solution was able to epoxidize the electron deficient GQD substrates via electrophilic addition reaction, which was similar to the epoxidation process in Fig. 5
                     : Firstly, H2O2 acted on the CC bonds of GQDs via electrophilic addition. When O in H2O2 was added to a C, the H attaching O was rearranged, followed by dehydration, and ring formation (Fig. 5). Under the catalytic effect of acid or alkali, epoxides would undergo ring-opening reaction (Fig. 6
                     ). However, the timely dialysis of the solution ensured that the majority of COC on the GQD surface maintained their stability. Therefore, our proposed post-fabrication epoxidation method was able to control a single type of epoxide functional group.
